history.text: Hello!
Hello! I hope you are well today. Have you heard of the movie Frozen?
I have not heard of the movie Frozen, what is it about?
It is about a fearless princess and her friends who try to find her estranged sister. Apparently the estranged sister has magical ice powers that trapped the whole town into an eternal winter.
Rotten Tomatoes gave it an 89%, which seems low compared to the Cinema Score of an A+
wow that is a little weird that it has such a low score on rotten tomatoes
Do they end up saving her sister?
I'm not sure, I have to read further as it seems like my data does not tell me...
I would assume so because it is a Disney movie
Oh, okay.
that is true when does the hero not win in disney movies!
do you think there will be a second movie?
Apparently the sisters' parents die in a sea storm! How terrible. And very Disney.
I think there might be. Critics seemed to love it
If Disney can make more money off of something then they're gonna do it.
I totally like that thinking!
It was written to move directly to Broadway it seems, so there's another cash cow!
so since this movie is a disney movie, im assuming its okay to show to all ages?
I believe so
Do you think you would watch it, even as an adult?
who stars in the movie in terms of the voices for there character
I think I would watch it, I love watching disney movies!
Kristen Bell voices 18 year old Anna, Idina Menzel is Elsa, and Jonathan Groff voices Kristoff (Anna's friend)
I am not really familiar with any of those names.
do you think this movie is full of action?
Excellent! I am all about watching movies about girls with crokinetic magic.
cryokinetic*
how many movies have girls with cryokinetic magic?
I think there is some action in it. The parents die towards the beginning, and Elsa the Ice Queen turns the entire town into an ice crazy town.
Not too many battles but some cool special effects.
I admire special effects!
I think there is only one movie with a girl with cryokinetic powers haha.
haha and do you think this movie has any comedy in it?
Critics say the middle of the movie is a bit jokey, so I'd say somewhat.
It was a pleasure talking to you today!

uid2response.feedback: The other user was very informative of the movie
